vdB130 region, IC 1318, LBN 208, NGC 6888; Cygnus
Astro-Physics 305mm f/3.8 Riccardi-Honders astrograph (Lum, Ha, OIII)
Takahashi FSQ-106 f/5 refractor (color)
KAF-16803 FLI Proline (Lum, Ha, OIII)
KAI-11002XCM SBIG STL (color)
Total Exposure Time: 12.6 hours L:OSC 140:195, NGC6888 Ha:OIII 180:240 minutes unbinned
July 2011, Inkom, ID

Comment: This is a hybrid-composite mosiac image using data from two different telescopes and cameras. vdB 130 is a small, faint, moderately red reflection nebula in the right upper quadrant of the image and surrounds the small open cluster of the same designation.  NGC 6888 has been enhanced with additional H-alpha and OIII data.
